Commentary: Beautifully stylish dress, and I love the pleating.
Can see here how the pleating comes round to the back to create some gathering at the back.

PhotoDetails1: Photo by Rodin Eckenroth/GA/The Hollywood Reporter via Getty Images

Commentary: Very Grecian and a beautiful colour on her. I was initially not sold on this dress, but it's one of those dresses that looks awkward in still photos, but looks fabulous in motion. Some of the following photos show that a little bit better.
This is a very statuesque garment. I like the use of pink as a contrast colour.
It's interesting, but the colours really clash badly with her skin tone (or her fake tan?)
I would imagine it'd be hard to choose formalwear as someone with alopecia because you might be tempted to go long-sleeved and cover up. I'm glad she hasn't here. I think she looks lovely.
Very delightful dress -- great colour, lovely lines.
Not a fan of the straight line as a low waist division point.
Cool chartreuse colour. (I think this is chartreuse....)
